body:
### Version of Hardhat

2.17.1 (other version may have this bug)

### What happened?

At first, I am a new bee to hardhat for just a few days, so maybe this is not a bug.

I am writing a time-related contract, so I set  `hardhat.config.ts[.js]` 's `config.networks.hardhat.mining.auto` = false and `interval: [2500, 3500]`

when i run tests with `await expect(fn()).to.be.revertedWith('ERC20: insufficient allowance');` 

It should be reverted and the `hardhat node` reported reverted, but `hardhat test` console tells me:

```
AssertionError: Expected transaction to be reverted
      + expected - actual

      -Transaction NOT reverted.
      +Transaction reverted.
```

I did a lot debug today, after many tries, I suddenly found out this optional, I set it back to true(enable automine), then It works!

### Minimal reproduction steps

I think you can just try hardhat starter project for test, just set hardhat.config.ts[.js] into this:
```ts
import { HardhatUserConfig } from "hardhat/config";
import "@nomicfoundation/hardhat-toolbox";

const config: HardhatUserConfig = {
  solidity: "0.8.19",
  networks: {
    hardhat: {
      mining: {
        auto: false,
        interval: [2500, 3500]
      }
    }
  }
};

export default config;
```
and run the test, the bug will show up, and it seems only affect `revertedWith()` I thought maybe the logical of dealing with transaction receipt is wrong somewhere

